Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.7 percent to
4,274.77 on April 20. The stock market was shut for holidays on
April 21 and 22.  Security Bank Corp. (SECB)  : The lender will replace
 China Banking Corp. (CHIB)   in the benchmark Philippine Stock
Exchange Index starting on May 9, based on a review of trading
activity from January to December 2010, the bourse said in a
statement posted on its website on April 20. Security Bank
increased 1.3 percent to 91 pesos. China Bank was unchanged at
436 pesos.  Semirara Mining Corp. (SCC)  : The largest Philippine coal
producer said its wholly owned unit SEM-Calaca Power Corp. will
pay a dividend of 15 centavos a share, a stock exchange filing
showed. The stock rose 0.6 percent to 215 pesos.  Vista Land & Lifescapes Inc. (VLL)  : The developerâ€™s low-
cost housing unit Lessandra will sell 12 billion pesos ($279
million) worth of projects this year, a stock exchange filing
showed. The stock increased 0.7 percent to 3.07 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
